Package oracle.cloudstorage.ftm.exception

Exceptions thrown by the API.

See: Description

  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    AuthenticationFailure
    Failed to authenticate with storage cloud service.
    ClientException
    Base class exception for any error from the API.
    ContainerNotEmpty
    Container is not empty.
    ContainerNotFound
    Container not found.
    ContainerSSEPolicyMismatch
    Object's container and segments container have different server-side encryption (SSE) policies.
    ContainerStorageClassValidationFailed
    Container storage class is incompatible with the storage class specified in upload/download configuration.
    DirectoryTraversalFailure
    IO Exception while recursively listing the files in a directory.
    FailedToCreateParentDirectory
    Failed to create parent directory for download.
    FileNotWritable
    Download destination file is not writable.
    FileSizeTooBig
    File size is too big and not supported by this utility.
    FileTransferMangerShutdown
    FileTransferManager has been shutdown.
    ForceDeleteContainerException  
    InvalidContainerName
    Invalid Container Name. Thrown when the container name is null or empty or contains a forward slash ('/').
    InvalidDestinationDirectory
    Invalid destination directory. The specified input is null or does not have permissions to write or cannot create directory.
    InvalidDestinationFile
    Invalid destination file specified. The input parameter for file is invalid if it is null or is not a normal file or its parent directory is not writable.
    InvalidMetadataInput
    Invalid meta-data input.
    InvalidObjectName
    Invalid object name. Thrown when the object name is null or empty or begins with a slash ('/').
    InvalidQueryParameterLimit
    Invalid value specified for the query parameter limit.
    InvalidSegmentSize
    Invalid segment size.
    InvalidSourceDirectory
    Invalid source directory for upload.
    Md5ChecksumFailed
    MD5 checksum verification failed.
    NoObjectsFound
    No objects found to download from specified container.
    NotAnArchiveContainer
    Container storage class is not Archive.
    NotEnoughSpaceInTempDir Deprecated
    As of release 2.1
    ObjectExists
    Object to be uploaded already exists in the container.
    ObjectNotFound
    Object not found.
    ObjectNotRestored
    Object is not restored.
    SegmentSizeTooSmall
    Segment size is too small which will result in more than maximum segment count for the file.
    ServiceException
    Represents HTTP error returned by the cloud storage service.
    UnsupportedSSEPolicy
    Server-side encryption (SSE) policy of an object's container is not supported. This exception is thrown by upload APIs when a segments' container cannot be created since a static-large object's container's SSE policy is other than BASE_ENCRYPTION policy.
